info.name: Filter Coffee
info.description: Indian filter coffee is a coffee drink made by mixing hot milk and sugar with the infusion obtained by percolation brewing of finely ground coffee powder in a traditional indian filter coffee. It has been described as "hot, strong, sweet and topped with bubbly froth" and is known as filter kaapi in india.

info.name: Poratha Kurma
info.description: Poratha is prepared from refined wheat flour. Feast this great recipe to your taste buds. Kurma is made of mixed vegetables with coconut and onion gravy.

info.name: Chaas
info.description: The classic chaas (chaach/mattha) also known as the indian version of buttermilk is a refreshingly cooling summer drink made with creamy yogurt and seasonings.

info.name: Idli Sambhar
info.description: Idli is a type of savoury rice cake, originating from south india, popular as a breakfast food in southern india. Idli is made by steaming a batter consisting of fermented black lentils (de-husked) and rice served with coconut chutney and sambar.

info.name: Medu Vada
info.description: Medu vada is a south indian breakfast snack made from vigna mungo (black lentil). It is usually made in a doughnut shape, with a crispy exterior and soft interior. A popular food item in south indian cuisine it is generally eaten as a breakfast or a snack.

info.name: Dil Kush Dosa
info.description: Dosa is made with four types of chutneys, mixed vegetables and fried noodles finished with cheese and paneer
